explanation: "Marked structure is the deep inguinal ring, formed by a defect in fascia transversalis.\nThe deep inguinal ring is an opening in the transversalis fascia present 1 cm above the inguinal ligament, midway between the anterior superior iliac spine and the pubic symphysis.\nAn indirect inguinal hernia arises through the deep inguinal ring, lateral to the inferior epigastric vessel.<br><br><br>\n<img src=\"https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/question_explanation/ec92b0d5-27f2-45c2-b623-fbca61854557.jpg\" alt=\"Uploaded Image\">",
