explanation: "The marked area in the image corresponds to the gastric impression on the anterior surface of the left kidney. The left kidney has several important anterior relations due to its position in the upper abdomen. These relations produce distinct impressions on the anterior surface of the kidney.<br><br>Important Anterior Relations of the Left Kidney<br><br>* Stomach \u2192 forms the gastric impression on the upper medial anterior surface.\n* Spleen \u2192 produces the splenic impression on the upper lateral part.\n* Pancreas (body) \u2192 lies anterior to the central region of the kidney.\n* Left colic flexure and jejunum \u2192 related to the inferior portion.",
