explanation: "In the given scenario of a patient with portal hypertension, anastomosis between esophageal veins and left gastric veins can be seen. In portal hypertension, increased pressure within the portal venous system may result in the dilation of portal venous tributaries and reversed flow at sites of portosystemic anastomoses.<br><br><br>\n<br>",
