explanation: "The marked structure lies in the **posterior cranial fossa near the occipital bone/venous sinuses**, whose dura is supplied by **upper cervical nerves (C2\u2013C3)**.\nPain from this region is therefore **referred to the occipital region and back of the neck**.",
