explanation: "The marked point in the image indicates the lateral pterygoid plate of the sphenoid bone. The muscle attached to the lateral surface of the lateral pterygoid plate is the **lateral pterygoid muscle**.<br><br><img src=\"https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/question_explanation/ab6a5994-9689-496a-a6ed-ef096ec656da.jpg\" alt=\"Uploaded Image\">",
