explanation: "The given image shows prominent **collagen fibers** arranged in bundles with intervening rows of **chondrocytes.** This is suggestive of white fibrocartilage.\nMicroscopy of fibrocartilage shows the following:<br><br>* Chondrocytes- Round in shape (in tendons they are flattened and elongated)\n* Ground tissue with collagen fibers- Type I collagen fibers\n* Absence of perichondrium<br><br>\n<img src=\"https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/question_explanation/1a8487e9-edc6-4a4f-9c64-2473629283f9.jpg\" alt=\"Uploaded Image\">",
