explanation: "This histological image shows a section of lung tissue displaying various components of the respiratory pathway. The marked structure represents a terminal bronchiole (terminal bronchus), which is characterized by its relatively thick muscular wall compared to the surrounding structures.\n**The respiratory pathway follows a hierarchical organization:** primary bronchus \u2192 secondary bronchus \u2192 tertiary bronchus (supplying bronchopulmonary segments) \u2192 terminal bronchioles \u2192 respiratory bronchioles \u2192 alveolar ducts \u2192 alveolar sacs \u2192 alveoli.<br><br><img src=\"https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/question_explanation/7db42f7a-ce4b-4aca-ba4f-c615da0aca04.jpg\" alt=\"Uploaded Image\">",
