tags: ["ZVRecommended", "PYQ", "INI-CET Nov 2025"],
text: "Which of the following does not have an endocrine component?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/questions_image/option/01KKDPB7Y9Y8ET3ZKGYCFWF7A6.jpg", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "B", "text": "https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/questions_image/option/01KKDPB80WEKWP0AB63R991BW3.jpg", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "C", "text": "https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/questions_image/option/01KKDPB83KPAMWPM5RT479M2MA.jpg", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/questions_image/option/01KKDPB861FTMBFRR8A5FHR0VC.jpg", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "The correct answer is **B (Uterus)**.\nTestis (A) has **Leydig cells**, ovary (C) has **follicles and corpus luteum**, and pancreas (D) has **islets of Langerhans**, all providing endocrine function.\nThe **uterus** is a purely **target organ for hormones** and has **no intrinsic endocrine component**.",
